r> <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3180.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3168.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top  class=headings><font color=#333399>Author</font></td><td valign=top  class=headings><font color=#333399>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucoadey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>coadey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/26/01 2:31:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Raid Resistance Gear - How much Save/Wis is Safe?</span><hr size=1> Hi all,<br>
<br>
Over the levels, I've aquired some decent gear to give me 200 wis, and an extra +200 or more Mana:<br>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2 Forest Loops, Velium Ruby Veil,<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Black Sapphire Platinum Necklace, Platinum Tiara,<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2 Velium Jasper Rings, 2 Withered Leather Wristbands,<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Withered Leather Arms, Withered Leather Gloves,<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Braided Ivy Cords, Mithril Runed Tunic,<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mammoth Hide Cloak, High Quality Blood Wolf Harness, <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Gatorscale Leggings, GEB's,<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Dark Ember, Book of Obolus, Frozen Orb<br>
<br>
Now that I'm 52, I'm starting to go on raids, but I'm somewhat inexperienced (having quad kited most of my life). Even though the above items were very time and money consuming to get, most don't give me any Saves.<br>
<br>
Some folks tell me, for raids, you should have a minimum of 70 on your Fire, Cold and Magic resists *Unbuffed*. Is that an accurate number?<br>
<br>
So, I'm trying to get some items to switch out during raids. I've only bought these so far:<br>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Crown of Froglok Kings (20 Fire, 20 Cold)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2 Diamond Platinum Wedding Rings (+7 to all, each)<br>
<br>
With those 3, my Magic is 44, Fire is 81 and Cold is 74, (Wis down to 186). Since I've also been told Wis isn't so important on raids, and my Magic is still low, I'm planning on getting the following also:<br>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2 Hollowed Bone Bracers (+7 Magic, each)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2 Earring of Magic Reflection (+5 Magic, each)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;White Gold Necklace (+7 Magic, Fire and Cold)<br>
<br>
Which will bring my unbuffed Magic to 75, Fire 88 and Cold 81 but drop my Wis down to 170. <br>
<br>
Is that a good place to be? Is the loss of 30 wis (312 mana @ 52), worth the extra 31 Magic protection? Can anyone suggest different items, for better stats?<br>
<br>
Advice from experienced druid raiders very appreciated!!<br>
(Blue Diamonds are too expensive/rare at the moment, so please only realistic suggestions :)<br>
<br>
Thanks! (Woof),<br>
<br>
Coadey of Veeshan<br>
<a href="http://www.keepersoflife.org">Keepers of Life</a> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucoadey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>coadey</A> at: 4/26/01 2:34:11 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufoolsfizzelmore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fools Fizzelmore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/26/01 10:44:05 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.reemst.com/calvin_and_hobbes/animated/pics/ani.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Resistance Gear - How much Save/Wis is Safe?</span><hr size=1> Hey there,<br>
<br>
<br>
Goto Temple of Droga and get the earring of essence (+10 sv magic). Also while there do yourself a favour and get the Shroud of Nature.(bring a friend like a tank..you will clear out all the spawns fast and get a shroud in 2-3 hours if lucky. I got 3 in about 6-7 hours, one for me and gave one to a friend and the third rotted...DOH!). The shroud is 13 ac 6 wis 7sv cold/fire/magic...and much better than the RMT in my opinion.<br>
<br>
[EDIT:- correction SoN is not Magic resist as someone pointed out...I was operating from memory and got it wrong....it is 13ac 6 wis 8fr 8cr :) ]<br>
<br>
Also do the locked run quest thingie...that is a nice necklace with resists and mana.<br>
<br>
Finially get a mistmore shield, nice resists on that one too. (or of course you can the book of rings, 8wis 10FR CR and swap out other slots instead).<br>
<br>
Personally If I am going on a raid where resists are important, I have no problem dropping my wis from 200+ down to 140ish. On a raid you will have crack and the mana pool s not half as important as staying alive to keep the tanks alive. More often than not you will not have a bard in your group so you need to get your resists as high as possible. Currently in our guild we have to have a min of 120 resist for all for the serious raids....and quite a few people over shoot this by a lot.<br>
<br>
Don't get hung up on resist gear...but there is LOTS of there that is good solid gear that is cheap to get....but your wis will suck. So unless you are a serious power gamer don;t worry about it...get resists up about the 80 mark and have fun.<br>
<br>
I am not sure what targets you are after, but don't wait till the last minute to start on you DR and PR also...My best advice is to start getting any all items that have good resists on them and store them on a mule in RV. When the time comes about for a raid you will be happy you got the resist stuff together nice and early!! you can then also play with the combinations and find what is best for you.<br>
<br>
Also, don;t forget for a raid, you only need your resist gear for the encounter. Wear your normal stuff for the 2-3 hours needed before hand to get to the target(eg clearing the FG's, IG's or whatever)..then Before the buffing start put on your gear.<br>
<br>
hope that helps :)<br>
<br>
Fools/Cuchullann. <p><P align=center><EM><STRONG><FONT color=blue size=4>Fools 
