Blood</EM></STRONG></FONT></P></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufoolsfizzelmore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fools Fizzelmore</A> at: 4/30/01 4:04:12 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umicewandu02.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Micewandu02</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/27/01 4:33:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Resistance Gear - How much Save/Wis is Safe?</span><hr size=1> I will take 140 wisdom and be alive, than 200 wisdom and be dead.  And that's about it in a nutshell. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uleandrasilvertongue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leandra Silvertongue</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/27/01 6:21:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Resistance Gear - How much Save/Wis is Safe?</span><hr size=1> I agree with mice - my natural wis sucks and when I go to raids, my Wis drops from 202 to 140 so that my resists can go up.  If you can get your BASE resists (before any buffs) to 100 on FR/CR/PR and 100 MR at the same time, take that instead of WIS.<br>
<br>
 <p><BR> Leandra  Silvertongue - Druid, 56  <BR> Proud member of <a href=http://pub49.ezboard.com/belysium55949>Elysium</a>  <BR>  <b>"Have you hugged a Druid today? =)" </b> <BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uellendilhsilvermist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellendilh Silvermist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/27/01 6:36:07 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~phiphix/ellendihlchibby.gif width=33 height=37></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Resistance Gear - How much Save/Wis is Safe?</span><hr size=1> I am usually around 150 WIS with resist gear on, with an added 300 mana. Never had a mana problem with C2/mask/potg.<br>
<br>
Also, a commonly used figure for minimum resistance is 100 unbuffed. Below that, you are taking some risks (or not, depending on the mob).<br>
<br>
I use mainly velium blue diamonds stuff, along with some dropped-off mobs gear. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukatlynel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katlynel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/27/01 9:20:00 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.asianavenue.com/indiegrrl/faedrake.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Resistance Gear - How much Save/Wis is Safe?</span><hr size=1> Good luck getting earrings of magic reflection, they're pretty rare and I don't think I've ever seen one auctioned.  (They're only gotten as a random reward off that Nilipuss quest.)<br>
<br>
Correction, the shroud of nature does *not* have 7svmagic ... only fire/cold.  A few other decent resist items include spectral shroud (back slot, 5 svmagic), symbol of loyalty to Vox (wrist 7svcold), and diamond resist mask (gold is 10fire/cold 5poison/dis, electrum is 5fire/cold 10poison/dis ... I went with electrum).  There's also the supple scale armband that drops (nodrop) off the Karnor's drolvarg warlord, though of course that would require you to actually group (gasp!) to get it.<br>
<br>
Also I'd consider going for pure MR in neck slot and one of the finger slots, I use a plat jacinth ring and plat wolf's eye agate necklace.  This is because MR items are so much rarer than other resists ... i.e., I can get other resists in many more item slots than i can get MR, so getting MR where I can get it is really important. <p><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2">
Katlynel Wolfcaller
<BR>54 Wanderer, <a href="http://www.aradani.com/warcouncil">The War Council</a>, Saryrn
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/27/01 9:26:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Resistance Gear - How much Save/Wis is Safe?</span><hr size=1> In addition, the meat that you get from Wyverns in Cobalt Scar can be turned into a food item that when eaten will give you +3 MR.<br>
<br>
Not bad for practically a freebie.  In addition there is other resist food as well.<br>
<br>
Valinn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uduranstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>duranstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/27/01 8:03:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Resistance Gear - How much Save/Wis is Safe?</span><hr size=1> Any suggestions for resist gear for:<br>
<br>
Back? I know a Lozidal shell shield would rock, but I'm not sure i can get one (anyone know what kind of group i would need to take the big turtle?)<br>
<br>
Belt?<br>
<br>
Shoulders?<br>
<br>
cheaper items and those giving MR would be better =) thanks<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucoadey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>coadey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/28/01 10:38:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shoulders</span><hr size=1> Well, for shoulders, I found Withered Leather Shoulders to be decent (STR+5 STA+5 MANA+15 SV POISON+3 SV DISEASE+3 SV COLD+3 SV FIRE+3 SV MAGIC+3). I'm wearing a lot of other withered, and each piece cost me exactly 1k, so I hope to pick some shoulders up for that or less.<br>
<br>
My Mammoth Hide Cloak gives Sv cold +5, and since I can't find any other nice black for my budget, I'm not going to replace it.<br>
<br>
Belt, I haven't found any with +resists. If anyone knows of a good belt piece, please post your reccomendations. :)<br>
<br>
The Locked Rum quest suggestion, which I found starts in Iceclad and yields a chain necklace, doesn't have stats as good as a player made necklace or even a White Gold necklace. So I'm going to try for one of the later two.<br>
<br>
Thanks for the help everyone. :)<br>
<br>
Coadey of Veeshan<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.keepersoflife.org">www.keepersoflife.org</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukatlynel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katlynel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/28/01 11:00:22 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.asianavenue.com/indiegrrl/faedrake.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shoulders</span><hr size=1> Back slot, I swap out between:<br>
Spectral Shroud (+5svmagic +5svpoison and I think ac5) 1-200ppish on Saryrn<br>
Kunzar Cloak (+10svfire ac7 wis2) also 1-200ppish<br>
Mammoth Hide Cloak (+5svcold ac7 wis4)<br>
I also have a cloak of the icebear (20svcold) that I rarely wear.<br>
<br>
Waist slot, there's very little ... splitpaw or gnome skin belt are +5svpoison, but other than that your only real option is the silverleaf girdle that drops in Hate (like 20MR) or else a tailored cobalt drake hide belt which is super hard to make and has a few sv cold points on it.<br>
<br>
Shoulders I use my obulus death shroud, it's +1 to all saves and its other stats are so good that I think it's worth keeping on.<br>
<br>
But in general, magic resist is very simply a pain in the arse to get, it's the hardest of all the resists to increase (MR items are the rarest and hardest to get), as well as the most useful of all the resists to have.  And therefore magic resist items are generally very expensive. <p><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2">
Katlynel Wolfcaller
<BR>54 Wanderer, <a href="http://www.aradani.com/warcouncil">The War Council</a>, Saryrn
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=faynedethe>Fayne Dethe</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/29/01 11:37:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Resistance Gear - How much Save/Wis is Safe?</span><hr size=1>   If possible, I'd try to keep wisdom in the 160-170 range so with an enchanter wisdom buff you wont be losing much mana.  However, to get decent resists you are going to need some items with good wisdom and resists.  Some easy Velious items to get for wisdom and resists are the Seal of Thoradin 3 ac 3 wis 30 mana 3 cold/magic resist ranged slot item (thurgadin quest), Kromnif Military Leggings 14 ac 6 wis and 5 cold/disease resist legs, and finally coldain military wristguard 10 ac 5 wis and 5 magic/5 cold resist.  Both the Kromnif military leggings and the wristguard can be multiquested with a friend who is allied with those factions.  Those quests can all be done solo but best to find a partner to help kill the end creature for leggings/wristguard.  A non-quest item to get for wisdom/resists in Velious is the wedding band 2 ac 5 wis 15 mana 8 fire/cold resist - it is found by killing the groom on the 5th floor of the Tower of Frozen Shadow (easily soloable).<br>
<br>
BTW, Hollowed Bone Bracer is arms not a bracer - go figure ;p.  If possible, try going on a few fear raids - the vermiculated arms are a VERY common drop and 7 magic resist/other stats (I am still wearing vermiculated arms, heh).  If you are incredibly lucky, you can get a vermiculated bracer with 8 fire/cold resist (I still havent gotten one after 10 million fear/hate raids ;p).  Also, a vermiculated tunic is very nice cause it has 13 wisdom which means you can forgo wisdom in alot of other areas.<br>
<br>
Some alternative bracers to vermiculated with resists include supple scale which drops off warlord in KC - 3 ac 5 wis 10 fire resist 15 mana, and bracer of vejaan 10 ac 10 fire/cold resist (no wisdom) - drops in Temple of Drogga from the same mob that drops the earring of essence (10 magic resist 30 hp earring) - go there to get the earring and hope you get lucky with bracer of vejaan cause it is really rare drop.  Probably alot easier just to buy the bracer of vejaaan ;p. <p>Fayne Dethe<BR> 
Level 59 Druid of Xegony<BR>
Havenlight</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upadainfain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Padain Fain</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/1/01 1:37:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Resistance Gear - How much Save/Wis is Safe?</span><hr size=1> Sarnak Battle Shield is great for resists and AC and it is sold/traded quite a bit these days. 10 heat/cold/magic is great.<br>
I use a Cloak of the Rygorr Oracles. Considering how hard it is to get the better cloaks (Heiro/Lodizal etc) its actually pretty good. 2wis, 10vs cold and 5vs magic plus a little mana. I also keep a Kunzar Cloak in the bank to change for 10 FR.<br>
Crown of the Froglok Kings can be had for around 1k these days so there's no excuse not to have its 20 FR/CR for raids.<br>
<br>
I am slightly torn between purchasing a Velium Diamond Ring for 8vs all and finding someone to make a Velium Blue Diamond Bracelette (30mana 9 FR/DR/PR/MR and 11 CR). Anyone know what the latter is likely to cost?<br>
<br>
Padain <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukatlynel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katlynel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/1/01 2:38:24 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.asianavenue.com/indiegrrl/faedrake.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Resistance Gear - How much Save/Wis is Safe?</span><hr size=1> On my server, diamonds go for about 500-1000pp and velium diamond rings might go for, damn, not sure how much the finished product would go for, a few k I guess ... Blue diamonds go for 3k and velium BD bracers go for 8k-9k. <p><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2">
