 Lets not forget a few pieces of resist gear<br>
 <br>
 Gladiator Chain Leggings - Legs have +10MR<br>
 Gladiator Arms - Arms are +2 all saves cept magic which<br>
 is +3.<br>
<br>
 Basically, as a druid, FR/CR should be pretty easy to<br>
 find since most of the items druids can wear have FR/CR<br>
 on them (go figure). With my normal equipment I have<br>
 102FR/98CR and I don't have any blue diamond jewelry.<br>
 My PR/DR are both in the 40's and MR is 51 so you could<br>
 say they all more or less stink but can be raised. You<br>
 can pick up little pieces of jewelcrafted resist gear<br>
 to swap out for particular raid types (for typical dragons<br>
 you need MR + whatever the dragon's breath is...MR is<br>
 almost more important since you don't want to die while<br>
 running to and fro from the dragon fear). As for trashing<br>
 wis, I have 212 wis at the moment (yes, I need to find<br>
 something better than what I have to swap out and get<br>
 back down to 200 ish) and when I swap out resist gear I<br>
 normally drop down to about 150s or 160s. I've never had<br>
 a mana shortage. I'm either dead or the mob drops so fast<br>
 I've done some DD, if I know I can stick them, or I've<br>
 healed whatever char the mob was beating on. When I first<br>
 went on a dragon raid I was ignorant of much of the resist<br>
 gear and I dropped like a stone in water. My 200+ wis did<br>
 me a world of good when I dropped 10 seconds into combat.<br>
<br>
 Manolas Autumnleaf<br>
 Druid of 58 seasons, Cazic Thule<br>
 Officer of Second Age <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usyldane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>syldane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/2/01 5:10:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Resistance Gear - How much Save/Wis is Safe?</span><hr size=1> Coadey, one small note about the hollowed bone bracers.  Strange as it may seem, they are for ARM, not your wrist, so you would only be able to use one of them.  They are good to have, especially on the PvP servers.  I guess that's one advantage of PvP servers.  By the time you get ready to go on plane raids, you have lots of resist armor usually! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upeoni.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Peoni</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/2/01 6:11:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Resistance Gear - How much Save/Wis is Safe?</span><hr size=1> For raid mobs like Vox/Nagafen at lvl 52 you will get by fine with a base 70-80MR and 100FR or CR (unbuffed)<br>
<br>
Against Kunark Dragons when you reach a level that you can really take part, that number rises drastically where 150+MR CR or FR (unbuffed) is a good target to aim for.<br>
<br>
As for resist items<br>
Froglok Crown 20FR/CR or tranix crown 20MR (Lguk/Solb)<br>
Earring of essence 10MR (Droga temple - quite easy to obtain)<br>
Gold Diamond Mask 10FR/CR 5PR/DR 3MR (Jewelcraft)<br>
Blue Diamond earrings (11PR/DR 6FR/CR 4MR) are also very good resist items (jewelcraft)<br>
White Gold Necklace 7FR/CR/MR (Lguk)<br>
Wurm Scale Coat 20FR 10MR (shoulders) from Burning Woods<br>
Verm Bracers - very good wisdom item and 7FR/CR with some mana (Plane of fear)<br>
Coldain military bracer (again good wisdom and AC - with 5MR/CR) - velius quests<br>
Blue diamond bracer +9FR/MR/DR/PR +11CR - jewelcraft<br>
Platinum/Velium Diamond rings (+7 or +8 all resists) - jewelcraft<br>
Verm Arms or Hollowed Bone Bracers (7MR) Plane of Fear/Najena <br>
Withered leather arms (4wisdom 10FR) - the hole<br>
Drakescale belt 10FR - (sol a) Silverleaf Girdle (20MR and +wisdom - Plane of hate)<br>
Shroud of Nature (6wisdom 8FR/CR) - Temple of Droga<br>
Cloak of ice bear (20CR), Kunzar Cloak (10FR 2wis - KC) - or when you drop lucky - Lodizal Shield (20FR/CR 10MR +10wis and 23ac - cobalt scar quest)<br>
Verm Legs (5wis 7PR - plane of fear) or Gladiator Chain (wis +MR - kael)<br>
<br>
I've never worn +resist boots, and i'm not aware of a resist pair of gloves that i'd change out for my coldain gloves - i did wear verm before tho for 7DR...<br>
<br>
The main problem you will face is a wis vs resist trade off, and as items that have both are very highly sought after, you will normally face alot of competition to obtain them, with that said tho, if your on a raid where you require resists - go with resists. <br>
<br>
It is afterall better for you to run OOM on a raid than to spend the entire fight feared or having to heal yourself from dragon fear/breath weapon.....<br>
<br>
